There are two shape files in this repository:

* The India Boundary Shape File depicts the Republic of India's border in accordance with survey of India documents. 

Including the recently developed Jammu and Ladakh, Dadar and Nagar Haveli, and Daman and Diu, 
the State Boundary shape file depicts the borders of 28 Indian states and 9 Union Territories.

The state of Jammu and Kashmir was divided into the Union Territory of Jammu and Kashmir and the Union Territory of Ladakh on October 31, 2019.
Union Territory of Dadra and Nagar Haveli and Union Territory of Daman and Diu were combined on January 26, 2020, 
from the former territories of Daman and Diu and Dadra and Nagar Haveli. Every modification is made in the current
